LOWRIEK@... writes:

>

> litlrooh@... writes:
>

> >
> >Does anyone else just LOVE their music? My kids introduced me to Good
> >Charlotte, Green Day and now Evanescence (not sure if I spelled it right).
>
> >And they *thought* the introduced me to Ozzy...LOL. Of course I had to
> >tell them that Ozzy's "been around" for a long long time!
> >

I live for music, I mean it is my sanity keeper especially in my car. I have
a Grand Marque Park Lane edition (If you dont know the car it is a retiree
car looks new but its not) with a chameleon stereo and a sub woofer. LOL

The teens go by us on the road thinking we are a bunch of old people (over
65) and they pull up beside us and hear Ozzy or a rap song it's a (quiet)
riot. I of coarse have to beat them out of a light too. lol

My son listens to everything now. Country, Rock, Hard rock, Classical you
name it.
I am still trying to be ok with M&M. He is trying to get used to Betty Davis
Eyes.

Nothing like Mom and son fly-n down the highway to go to B & N blaring Ice
Ice Baby, lol. Ahh what a great life it tizzz.

Laura D

<A HREF="www.whimsicaltoys.com">www.whimsicaltoys.com</A>

I have not heard Evanescence. I am however hooked on Ozzy, and my 7 yr old ds
thinks he is the coolest also. I also love Pink, Linkin Park, Sum 41, Swollen
Members, Gob, the list goes on and on.I am enjoying experiencing the music
with my son. I Love to hear his take on music. At the same time, he loves to
listen to a classical disc we have called "Baby Dance", that is a variety of
composers.
Neat subject to talk about.
Nancy

messages.subject: Evanescence
messages.msgSnippet: Does anyone else just LOVE their music?  My kids introduced me to Good Charlotte, Green Day and now Evanescence (not sure if I spelled it right).  And they
messages.messageBody:
Does anyone else just LOVE their music? My kids introduced me to Good Charlotte, Green Day and now Evanescence (not sure if I spelled it right). And they *thought* the introduced me to Ozzy...LOL. Of course I had to tell them that Ozzy's "been around" for a long long time!

I bought the E. CD today and their lyrics are just incredible!!!

Just had to share.

Kristen
